Why the metaphor works for ideas

Your comparison actually maps pretty well to knowledge refinement loops.

First pass:
	•	raw ideas
	•	messy conversation
	•	partial understanding

Second pass:
	•	reflection
	•	restructuring
	•	extracting nutrients (insights)

In research or engineering this often looks like:
	1.	brainstorm
	2.	write it down
	3.	revisit and refine
	4.	produce the useful structure

So the “rabbit loop” metaphor is basically iterative digestion of ideas — the system extracts more value the second time through.

